<TITLE> Incoming EU presidency affirms Turkey entry goal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BRUSSELS, June 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Portugal, due to take over the presidency of the European Union at the weekend, affirmed on Thursday that membership was the goal of negotiations with Turkey rather than any limited partnership option. "All accession negotiations have one goal: accession, once all the criteria have been fulfilled," Lobo Antunes, secretary of state for European affairs, told a news briefing. "Agreements signed by member states must be respected," he added of the decision to open membership talks with Turkey in October 2005. French President Nicolas Sarkozy says he sees no place in Europe for the large, mainly Muslim country and advocates a form of partnership instead. He wants a debate on where the EU's borders lie later this year, but Antunes reiterated that the six-month Portuguese presidency did not see such a discussion as a priority. "We have more urgent dossiers to handle in the immediate future," he sa
